WEBVTT

00:12:59.200 --> 00:13:01.696
If we're in a social situation,

00:13:01.720 --> 00:13:05.456
we often can default to just saying,

00:13:05.480 --> 00:13:07.616
"If I took a risk here
and showed a weakness,

00:13:07.640 --> 00:13:09.056
that might affect my status."

00:13:09.080 --> 00:13:12.856
So this teeter-totter that goes on

00:13:12.880 --> 00:13:14.416
literally in our brains,

00:13:14.440 --> 00:13:18.736
but also in our social
environment -- we're torn.

00:13:18.760 --> 00:13:23.616
AG: But when I talk to groups about
how important it is to be vulnerable first

00:13:23.640 --> 00:13:25.336
before they build trust,

00:13:25.360 --> 00:13:28.000
they kind of look
like they've just seen a ghost.

00:13:28.720 --> 00:13:30.936
And I hear people say things like,